────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  VERDICT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The 3D identity system milestone introduced a well-designed, composable
architecture. The geometry / material / effects separation is correct and
provides a solid foundation for future iteration. No breaking architectural
changes are recommended.

Two issues require immediate attention:
  → R-QUAL-01: The Infinity component cannot process drag input in "engaged"
    state. This is a behavioral regression vs. the TorusKnot it replaced.
  → R-ARCH-01: TorusKnot and its supporting types should be removed to
    eliminate the confusion between the legacy and current identity objects.

All other findings are low-risk cleanups that improve maintainability
and polish without risk to stability.

No breaking changes are introduced by any of the recommendations above.
All refactors are backwards-compatible within the scope of this codebase.

